Tags.string 'NodeComment': Try to make the UI event driven and avoid binding if you can. Here we get the coin amount from the instance at start and assign an update function to an event dispacther the instance fires when coins get updated.
Its a function as we call this from the init and from the OnCoinUpdated event.
The game mode calls this, when the game gets saved. It is only playing a widget animation to show it and then it fades out

This hud shows the amount of orbs the player has gathered and has a small hint when the game saves. As the saving takes nearly no time it only triggeres a small animation that stay for a short time.
The widget also contains the BPW_Controls widget that has a hint what to press to spawn a new robot. The player controler triggers it to change when it detects a gamepad or keyboard input. But thats a bit hacky. Check the comments in PC_InGame.
